added.title: Ghostboy
added.description: Starfire mistakenly thinks she's killed Beast Boy, leading him to pose as a ghost and torment her.

added.title: The Best Robin
added.description: When the other Titans are too lazy to fight Brother Blood, Robin calls on his secondary team: Team Robin, a crime-fighting group made up of different Robins.

added.title: Operation Tin Man
added.description: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

added.title: Batman vs. Teen Titans: Dark Injustice
added.description: The Titans try to outprank each other on April Fools' Day.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The Tag
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get caught in the middle of Dad and Mr Robinson's trashcan feud.

added.title: The Game
added.description: The Wattersons embark on their first family game of Dodge or Dare, but soon find out why Gumball and Darwin abandoned the monster they created.

added.title: The Oracle
added.description: Banana Barbara has made a prophecy which Gumball simply cannot accept. Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Banana Joe's mom paints pictures which predict the future. When they find one that depicts Gumball running naked through the mall, Gumball is determined not to let it come to pass. However events conspire against him, and Gumball learns that sometimes you can't fight fate.

added.title: The Uploads
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to tear themselves away from the internet, but end up falling down the Elmore Stream-hole.

added.title: The Dream Team
added.description: Craig and his cousin, Bryson, join forces for an action packed weekend at their grandparents house.

added.title: Fire & Ice
added.description: Kelsey and Stacks write a story for book club, which turns out to be more personal than Kelsey realized.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: The Children of the Dog
added.description: Craig has tried to convince his family to get a dog for years but has never been successful, but he may have a chance if he follows the guidance of a charismatic creek kid and her three step program.

added.title: Look Who's Clocking
added.description: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

added.title: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
added.description: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Falafel's Passion
added.description: Apple and Onion try to help Falafel find his passion but it looks like things might take a humiliating turn.

added.title: Hole In Roof
added.description: Suddenly the hole in the roof is no longer a laughing matter but one of a life or death.

added.title: Patty's Law
added.description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

added.title: The Eater
added.description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

added.title: Champion
added.description: Stuck with a problematic pet, Apple and Onion need to somehow find a way to get their lives back.

added.title: DNA, A-OK!
added.description: Yogi finds out he's genetically a cat and joins Top Cat's gang.

added.title: Face of the Town!
added.description: Mayor Huckleberry holds a city-wide contest to find out which Jellystone citizen most represents the town.

added.title: Roundabout
added.description: Forever Knight finally assembles his Round Table of young but super-powerful Knights, including Ben? With his squires' help, Forever Knight turns a Particle Accelerator into a Time Machine and sets out to conquer all of history, but a certain hero with a team of 10 aliens on his side has other plans foiling Forever Knight at every twist and turn in time while Grandpa Max, Gwen and Phil keep the rest of the Round Table busy in the present.

added.title: Forever Road
added.description: During a drag race, Ben hopes to stay neck and neck with Vin Ethanol and La Grange as XLR8, but when his watch keeps shorting out, our hero must get creative if he is to keep up with his fast and furious foes!

added.title: Prey or Play
added.description: After receiving a super-exclusive ticket to Adrenaland, Ben leaves behind Grandpa Max and Gwen to enjoy the perks of being the parks only attendant, but when he learns he's not alone, our hero must now contend with the only kid who could afford the price of admission: Billy Billions!

added.title: The Night Ben Tennyson Came to Town
added.description: Team Tennyson travels to Wheeler, "the liveliest mining town on Route 66", but when Ben becomes paranoid that the Forever Knight is out to get him, he must try to convince his fam while also stopping his new foe from destroying the town.

added.title: Fear in the Family
added.description: Ben and Gwen can't wait for the Omni-Copter to arrive at the Great Pyramids, but when bad weather disrupts their flight, they soon come face-to-face with The Fogg and its spawn: The Fogg Family!

added.title: Melancholic Megalomaniac
added.description: Elliott and Mo try to cheer up Lord Kallous, with the help of someone from his past.

added.title: Diminishing Discourse
added.description: Elliott and Frankie decide to tell Mo about what really happened to the dinosaurs.

added.title: #AdventuresInBunnysitting
added.description: Zee asks Kara to look after her two magical bunnies, which quickly start to multiply, wreaking havoc all across Metropolis.

added.title: #HateTriangle
added.description: When Hal's ex-girlfriend shows up at the Metropolis High homecoming game and goes love-ballistic as the villain Star Sapphire, Jessica begins to second-guess her own nonviolent tactics.

added.title: #BurritoBucket
added.description: Babs loves her job at fast food restaurant Burrito Bucket, but her boss, who's fed up with her chronic lateness and bad case of scatterbrain, would love any excuse to fire her. When a bank robbery breaks out right across the street from work, Babs is torn between her role as a superhero and dutiful Burrito Bucket employee. Will she be able to save the day and keep her job all in the nick of time?

added.title: #MeetTheCheetah
added.description: Barbara Minerva is super-jealous of  "little Miss Perfect" Diana Prince. But when she uses an ancient artifact from her dad's collection to place a curse on Diana, it turns out that Diana's not the one who's cursed. It's Barbara.

added.title: #Beeline
added.description: When she stumbles across a villainous plot to blow up a bridge, Bumblebee shies from the challenge of taking on the baddies and reaches out to her friends. But when the other heroes are all indisposed, it'll take every ounce of courage Bumblebee has to rise to the occasion … despite being the smallest of the bunch.

added.title: Ralph
added.description: Charlie meets a creature just like him named Ralph. Charlie loves having a new friend, but the Bears think Ralph is bad news.

added.title: The Mall
added.description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

added.title: Cousin Jon
added.description: When the Bears attend Chloe's family reunion, they fall victim to the mischievous pranks of Chloe's cousin, Jon.

added.title: More Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through another video browsing session online, we get more videos uploaded by the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: The Zoo
added.description: Steven visits a special zoo.

added.title: That Will Be All
added.description: Steven and the Gems make a daring escape!

added.title: The New Crystal Gems
added.description: Connie helps look after Beach City while Steven is busy.

added.title: Restaurant Wars
added.description: Steven must help the Frymans and the Pizzas settle a reignited rivalry between their restaurants.

added.title: Monster Reunion
added.description: Steven reunites with an old friend.

added.title: Summer Fun Day!
added.description: The Thundercats are exhausted from fighting bad guys all the time so Lion-O suggests they spend a relaxing summer fun day at the beach, with no fighting! Unfortunately the beach is home to the Crabmen, giant, clawed humanoids that fight anyone who steps on their sand! Looks like summer fun day might involve some fighting!

added.title: Safari Joe
added.description: While minding her own business, Cheetara is caught in a trap set by Safari Joe, the famously annoying hunter! After escaping, she rallies the other ThunderCats to help her stop Joe once and for all, by turning the tables and capturing him!

added.title: Ratar-O
added.description: The ThunderCats have gotten so good at defeating the Mutants of Plun-Darr that it's basically become routine. That all changes with the arrival of the Mutants' old leader: Ratar-O, wielder of the Sword of Plun-Darr! Uh-oh!

added.title: Prince Starling's Quest
added.description: Lion-O is happily playing with Snarf in their "Frolicking Field" and doesn't have a care in the world, unfortunately he's accidentally stomping all over the miniature village of the Micrits! The tiny people want to defeat the "giant orange monster" but such a quest would require a brave hero. Luckily, the Micrits have such a hero: Prince Starling! Now, let us the tell you the epic tale of Prince Starling as he journeys to find the fountain of growth and defeat the wicked Lion-O, who has no idea any of this is going on!

added.title: Lion-S
added.description: Lion-O and the other ThunderCats are thrilled to meet a brand new Thunderian: Lion-S! She's cool, good at fighting robots and, most importantly, thinks Lion-O and his Sword of Omens are really neat and interesting! Looks like the ThunderCats have a new best friend! Maybe even, a new ThunderCat?????

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: The Son of Lilly
added.description: The battle for the fate of Shintaro Mountain concludes!

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: Adoradad
added.description: When AD's dad forbids her from working with the Sheriff's Dept because it's too dangerous, AD sets out to prove that she can take care of herself.

added.title: Badge-a-fire Explosion
added.description: When BC comes out of a rare state of hyper-focused creativity, he may have made something that could destroy all of PHV.

added.title: Zing Your Heart Out
added.description: When Adorabat starts to aggressively heckle everyone with her new zing power, she threatens the entire kingdom.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: That Slobot Is No Bot of Mine
added.description: Axel and the team compete against themselves in tests of skill, strength, and stamina, but when SloBot gets belittled, he splits into three separate robots - each with their own evil personalities!

added.title: Bowling for Ballers
added.description: Axel and the team must intervene when Zoe's not-so-friendly bowling competition with Cleo LeBall gets interrupted by Madcap, Porcupunk, and their new cohort, the mischievously magnetic Dynamo.

added.title: Countdown
added.description: Axel has to clean up the living room in time for his uncle's dinner party, but trying to do too much at once leaves him stuck as a toy with Orangutank on the loose and less than an hour until the guests arrive.

added.title: Joke's on You, Bro!
added.description: Axel and the team turn Galileo's camouflaging pranks around on him, convincing the gullible gecko that he's permanently invisible - to disastrous results!

added.title: Out of My Head
added.description: Axel must help Sarge and Bobbie learn to walk in each other's shoes - literally - after Luka unwittingly switches the toys' heads!

added.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
added.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

added.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
added.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

added.title: Nightmare/Bad Dan
added.description: Nightmare: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning. It turns out, Dan's dreams have been hijacked by Haavik, who's trying to spread his vision of chaos and destruction to Dan!/Bad Dan: Haavik has taken control of Dan and sends him on a Bakugan rampage! With "Bad Dan" causing all kinds of havoc and destruction, the rest of the Awesome Brawlers have no choice but to roll out to try to contain "Bad Dan".

added.title: Dusk Industries Under Attack/Taking Dan Back
added.description: Dusk Industries Under Attack: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction./ Taking Dan Back: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

added.title: Who's the Fake?!/Trouble Busters! 2
added.description: With the reveal that Haavik is a shapeshifting Alien, the ABs start to get super-paranoid, realizing that ANYONE could be Haavik in disguise. The suspicion quickly turns inward, and the ABs are left wondering if they have an imposter among them!/ A kid brawler named Oliver has lost his Bakugan! This seems like a job for the Trouble Busters. The Awesome Brawlers help him chase down and try to catch the elusive Bakugan, who leads them on a wild goose chase through Los Volmos.

added.title: The Escape Room of Doom
added.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

added.title: Last One There
added.description: When Unikitty accidentally invokes an ancient curse, the gang must beat Master Frown and Brock back to the castle before one of them literally turns into a rotten egg.

added.title: The Very Best Candy
added.description: The gang can't decide which of their candy is the best, so they turn it sentient and have it fight to determine the winner.

added.title: The Unikingdom Awards
added.description: Unikitty throws an elaborate award show for everyone in the Unikingdom, including Master Frown and Brock, but tensions rise when Frown fails to win an award.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays
added.description:
Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day./
Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

added.title: Red Action 3: Grudgement Day
added.description: KO and Enid attempt to prevent a mysterious power battle between Rad and Red Action.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Dendy's Video Channel
added.description: Dendy tries to update KO's Video Channel for him, but has trouble finding something to post.

added.title: Let's Fight to the End
added.description: When a fighting tournament is announced at the Plaza, there is more at stake than meets the eye.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
added.description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: And Then There Were None
added.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Chess Master Steve
added.description: Pizza Steve goes to great lengths in order to beat Mr. Gus at a game of chess.

added.title: Tiny Miracle's Tiny Miracle
added.description: Upon seeing the gang have a fun time swimming and eating ice cream, Tiny Miracle realizes he wants to be a real boy.

added.title: Uncle Greedpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in need of some extra cash, so he starts charging for his services.

added.title: Exquisite Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa has been having some truly bizarre night terrors.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa: The High School Years
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and friends go way back to when they were in high school together.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Mas del canal de todos
added.description: A través de otra sesión de navegación por Internet, vemos más videos subidos por los Osos y sus amigos.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: El Benefactor
added.description: Los Osos ayudan a Chloe a presentar su proyecto de ciencias para un concurso escolar. Pero el rival de Chloe complica las cosas.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: El Centro Comercial
added.description: Los Osos van al centro comercial y se encuentran con sus equivalentes humanos.

added.title: El primo Jon
added.description: Cuando los Osos asisten a una reunión con la familia de Chloe, se convierten en víctimas de Jon, el travieso primo de Chloe.

added.title: Ralph
added.description: Charlie conoce a una criatura igual a él llamada Ralph. A Charlie le encanta tener un amigo nuevo, pero los Osos piensan que Ralph no trae nada bueno entre manos.

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Prankless
added.description: The guys want to win a prank war with a rival park.

added.title: La noche que Ben Tennyson vino al pueblo
added.description: El equipo Tennyson viaja a Wheeler, "la ciudad minera más animada de la Ruta 66". Pero cuando Ben se pone paranoico con la idea de que el Caballero por Siempre lo esté persiguiendo, debe tratar de convencer a su familia al mismo tiempo que evita que su nuevo enemigo destruya la ciudad.

added.title: Miedo en la Familia
added.description: Ben y Gwen están ansiosos por que el Omni-Copter llegue a las Grandes Pirámides. Pero cuando el mal tiempo interrumpe su vuelo, pronto se enfrentan cara a cara con Neblina y sus engendros: iLa familia Niebla!

added.title: Carretera por Siempre
added.description: Durante una carrera de aceleración, Ben espera mantenerse al mismo nivel con Vin Etanol y La Grange como XLR8. Pero cuando su reloj hace cortocircuito una y otra vez, nuestro héroe debe ser creativo si quiere seguir el ritmo de sus rápidos y furiosos enemigos.

added.title: Caza o Juego
added.description: Después de recibir un billete superexclusivo para Adrenalandia, Ben deja atrás al abuelo Max y a Gwen para disfrutar de las ventajas de ser el único asistente del parque. Pero pronto se entera de que no está solo.

added.title: See You There
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that everyone has been invited by Muscle Man to High Five Ghost's birthday party except them. They decide to go anyway.

added.title: Los Maestros Nunca se Rinden
added.description: Cole, la princesa Vania, Wu y los humildes llegan a un templo, que una vez fue un campo de entrenamiento para los Maestros Elementales de la Tierra.

added.title: La Hora Mas Oscura
added.description: Los Ninjas, los Munces y los Geckles se refugian en la Cueva Fuerte Geckle , pero enfrentan al Hechicero Calavera y al Dragón Grief-Bringer.

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los de Arriba Contra Atacan
added.description: Cole y los de abajo llegan para rescatar a los Ninjas. Para ello, Cole tendrá que recuperar las espadas legendarias, las Espadas de la Liberación.

added.title: Ninos del Perro
added.description: Craig ha intentado que su familia adopte un perro durante años, pero nunca lo logró. Puede que ahora tenga una oportunidad si sigue los consejos de un carismático niño del bosque y su programa de tres pasos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Hijo de Lilly
added.description: iLa batalla por el destino de la Montaña Shintaro concluye!

added.title: El baile de los Infusionistas
added.description: Los Infusionistas organizan un baile e invitan a todos los habitantes del bosque. Craig cree que el único propósito del baile es hacerle una broma a él, mientras que Kelsey debe lidiar con un admirador indeseado.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pijamada en casa de JP
added.description: JP invita a sus amigos para una pijamada, pero resulta ser la misma noche que un gran juego con linternas en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Te Quiero Mao Mao
added.description: Un solitario explosivo y su mejor amigo holgazán se desvían del viaje que los llevará a convertirse en leyenda y descubren que su historia apenas comienza.

added.title: La Aventura Perfecta
added.description: Cuando a Mao Mao se le antoja vivir la aventura perfecta, Adorabat dice una mentira piadosa.

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: #LosConejosMágicos
added.description: Cuando Zee le pide a Kara que cuide a sus dos conejitos mágicos, pronto comienzan a multiplicarse y a desatar el caos por toda Metrópolis.
